snippet.textDisplay:
this song reminds me of Karl Popper’s approach to the problem of induction as well! especially about his example with swans!

“you may see a white swan several times and think that all swans are white, not because you have any proof but because that is what you have seen all this time and you have gotten used to it. but when you happen to see a single black swan it will prove to you that not all swans are white and thus you will be able to falsify the self-made theory that all swans are white.

bts portrays this particular example because by being “black swans” they prove their uniqueness and go beyond the already-set borders of the music industry and the thoughts of the general public. they break asian stereotypes along with the stereotypes set for idols. by being black swans they prove that not all swans are white, which could also be regarded as poc representation in some sense (if you really wanna stretch it out) . just some thoughts :)
